 id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Sorensen, Andrew &amp; Swift, Ben (2013) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://extempore.moso.com.au/extras/cmj-2013.pdf\">Livecoding\u2019s many meanings</a> in Computer Music Journal. Vol 38(1), Spring 2014. pp 65-76</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">McLean, Alex (2014) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2633638.2633647\">Making programming languages to dance to: live coding with tidal</a> in Proceedings of FARM '14 Proceedings of the 2nd ACM SIGPLAN international workshop on Functional art, music, modeling &amp; design. pp 63-70</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Mark_Guzdial\" title=\"Mark Guzdial\">Mark Guzdial</a> (2013) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://computinged.wordpress.com/2013/10/01/live-coding-systems-challenge-cs-to-think-about-expression-again/\">Live coders challenge CS to think about expression again</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://gibber.mat.ucsb.edu/credits\">Gibber Credits</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Roberts, Charlie (2012) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hdl.handle.net/2027/spo.bbp2372.2012.011\">Gibber: Live Coding Audio in the Browser</a> in Proceedings of the 2012 International Computer Music Conference, Ljubljana.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Xambo, Anna; Freeman, Jason; Magerko, Brian; and Shah, Pratik (2016) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://users.sussex.ac.uk/~thm21/ICLI_proceedings/2016/Papers/Long_Papers/94_Live_Coding_Classroom.pdf\">Challenges and New Directions for Collaborative Live Coding in the Classroom</a> in Proceedings of International Conference on Live Interfaces, University of Sussex, Brighton.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F2--JzAvPsg\">WulfCode</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Blackwell, Alan &amp; Aaron, Sam (2015) <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://zenodo.org/record/19318/files/73_Craft_Practices_of_Live_Coding_Langua.pdf\">Craft Practices of Live Coding Language Design</a> in the Proceedings of the First International Conference on Live Coding, Leeds, UK</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ixi_lang&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><span class=\"official-website\"><span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ixi-software.net\">Official website</a></span></span></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2164\nCached time: 20180918111503\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.208 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.246 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 618/1000000\nPrepr